resources.description:
Companies API allows to register legal people on the database. It starts validating the input data by our KYC policy, then it is needed to upload some required documents. After that, it is just needed to wait for approval. It is possible to list basic information of a registered company on the database and filter results by registration ID, company ID, company documents and status as well as search for a partner in a specific company by using its national registration. If needed, it is also possible to change information about a company register by using its registrationId or companyId.

A brief resume of what Companies API does is shown below:

- Receive given information about the company and the partners;
- Basic validation (‚ÄúnationalRegistration‚Äù algorithm, empty mandatory fields, invalid data format, invalid terms and conditions or privacy policy tokens);
- Individual partners bureau validation using our KYC policy (name, mother name, birth date and national registration status);
- Status: waiting for documents (returns code 201:waiting_documents);
- Receive uploaded documents;
- Basic validation (empty mandatory fields and invalid data format);
- Status: waiting for approval (returns code 200:waiting_approval);
- Basic validation (valid request ID);
- If the request ID is valid, the process is finished (returns code 200:ok).

> Check the documentation [here](https://s3.amazonaws.com/dock-docs.caradhras.io/Companies+-+Documentation+(1).pdf) for additional information
